                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4306: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-30T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 30, 1933—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 31—12:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>417. The University Student Assembly this afternoon was attended by about 1,500
                    students. The meeting from beginning to end was in continuous disorder. Chibas,
                    a member of the Directorate, was permitted to make a speech, not in that
                    capacity, but solely as a student. He announced that the Directorate had
                    delivered an ultimatum to Grau San Martín “to change the identity of the
                    government” before November 4th and requested those supporting the Directorate
                    to leave the hall with him. About 100 left with him. The remaining 1,400
                    students are still in session. All of these oppose the government and the
                    Directorate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
